The paper deals with optimization problems related to matching algorithms, which are commonly studied in the fields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI), data structures (cs.DS), game theory (cs.GT), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), and computational complexity (cs.CC). The Stable Roommates problem is a classic problem in the field of matching algorithms, and the paper introduces two optimization variants of the problem, which are likely to be of interest to researchers in these sub-categories.
